description: Lists the partnerships associated with your Amazon Web Services account for your current or specified region. A partnership represents the connection between you and your trading partner. It ties together a profile and one or more trading capabilities.

nested_items.name: partnerships
nested_items.description: Specifies a list of your partnerships.

nested_items.name: profileId
nested_items.description: Returns the unique, system-generated identifier for the profile connected to this partnership.

nested_items.name: partnershipId
nested_items.description: Returns the unique, system-generated identifier for a partnership.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: Returns the name of the partnership.

nested_items.name: capabilities
nested_items.description: Returns one or more capabilities associated with this partnership.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: capabilityOptions
nested_items.description: Contains the details for an Outbound EDI capability.

nested_items.name: outboundEdi
nested_items.description: A structure that contains the outbound EDI options.

nested_items.name: interchangeControlHeaders
nested_items.description: In X12 EDI messages, delimiters are used to mark the end of segments or elements, and are defined in the interchange control header.

nested_items.name: senderIdQualifier
nested_items.description: Located at position ISA-05 in the header. Qualifier for the sender ID. Together, the ID and qualifier uniquely identify the sending trading partner.

nested_items.name: senderId
nested_items.description: Located at position ISA-06 in the header. This value (along with the senderIdQualifier) identifies the sender of the interchange.

nested_items.name: receiverIdQualifier
nested_items.description: Located at position ISA-07 in the header. Qualifier for the receiver ID. Together, the ID and qualifier uniquely identify the receiving trading partner.

nested_items.name: receiverId
nested_items.description: Located at position ISA-08 in the header. This value (along with the receiverIdQualifier) identifies the intended recipient of the interchange.

nested_items.name: repetitionSeparator
nested_items.description: Located at position ISA-11 in the header. This string makes it easier when you need to group similar adjacent element values together without using extra segments.

nested_items.name: acknowledgmentRequestedCode
nested_items.description: Located at position ISA-14 in the header. The value '1' indicates that the sender is requesting an interchange acknowledgment at receipt of the interchange. The value '0' is used otherwise.

nested_items.name: usageIndicatorCode
nested_items.description: Located at position ISA-15 in the header. Specifies how this interchange is being used:
T indicates this interchange is for testing.
P indicates this interchange is for production.
I indicates this interchange is informational.

nested_items.name: functionalGroupHeaders
nested_items.description: The functional group headers for the X12 object.

nested_items.name: applicationSenderCode
nested_items.description: A value representing the code used to identify the party transmitting a message, at position GS-02.

nested_items.name: applicationReceiverCode
nested_items.description: A value representing the code used to identify the party receiving a message, at position GS-03.

nested_items.name: responsibleAgencyCode
nested_items.description: A code that identifies the issuer of the standard, at position GS-07.

nested_items.name: delimiters
nested_items.description: The delimiters, for example semicolon ( ;), that separates sections of the headers for the X12 object.

nested_items.name: componentSeparator
nested_items.description: The component, or sub-element, separator. The default value is : (colon).

nested_items.name: dataElementSeparator
nested_items.description: The data element separator. The default value is * (asterisk).

nested_items.name: segmentTerminator
nested_items.description: The segment terminator. The default value is ~ (tilde).

nested_items.name: validateEdi
nested_items.description: Specifies whether or not to validate the EDI for this X12 object: TRUE or FALSE.

nested_items.name: tradingPartnerId
nested_items.description: Returns the unique, system-generated identifier for a trading partner.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: Returns a timestamp for creation date and time of the partnership.

nested_items.name: modifiedAt
nested_items.description: Returns a timestamp that identifies the most recent date and time that the partnership was modified.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: When additional results are obtained from the command, a NextToken parameter is returned in the output. You can then pass the NextToken parameter in a subsequent command to continue listing additional resources.
